cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing tasks such as relation extraction. The use of graph convolutional networks and dependency trees also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper's focus on pruning strategies and efficiency could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories.
